================================================================================
PRIOR ART DECLARATION — ESTABLISHED 2026-03-29
================================================================================

This repository constitutes documented prior art for the following innovations:

1. TERNARY WEIGHT ARCHITECTURE {0, 1, 3}
   - Void (0), Unit (1), Prime (3) discrete weight quantization
   - Straight-through estimator (STE) training for asymmetric ternary weights
   - Identity-biased initialization for deep discrete networks

2. ITERATIVE FIXED-POINT INFERENCE
   - Discrete weight networks converge iteratively (3-5 passes)
   - Continuous (fp16/fp32) networks do not converge iteratively
   - Convergence as a coherence/comprehension signal

3. TRAINING-AS-FILTRATION (COMPRESSION DYNAMICS)
   - Discrete models compress during training (eff rank decreases)
   - Continuous models diffuse during training (eff rank increases)
   - Compression trajectory: exploration → crystallization → annealing → saturation
   - Spectral gap peak-then-settle as annealing signature

4. STRUCTURED ABSENCE (ZERO-PATTERN INFORMATION)
   - Arrangement of zero-weights carries computational information
   - Permuting zero positions degrades performance 87-201%
   - Zero topology measurable via persistent homology (H0/H1)

5. DEPTH-FIRST SCALING WITH IDENTITY INITIALIZATION
   - Deep {0,1,3} networks require identity-biased init (95%+ ones)
   - LR warmup for discrete deep networks
   - 48-layer {0,1} crystal achieves coherent language generation

6. SIMPLICIAL SHEAF ARCHITECTURE
   - Neural network as simplicial complex with discrete transport maps
   - Sheaf-valued computation: weights as sections, ker(L_F) as output
   - Zeta-derivative zeros as convergence criterion analog

All experimental results, code, and documentation in this repository serve as
timestamped evidence of independent discovery and reduction to practice.

